3007 SV_FL_NOINTERP = 0x001000, /* no interpolation, eg. nodes */
3008 SV_FL_VOFINTERP = 0x002000, /* requires geometric interpolation, eg. vof */
3009 SV_FL_RESIDUAL = 0x004000, /* stores resiudal of a solved equation */

3012};

3029#define NO_COPY_MESH_SVAR(_nv) ((_nv == SV_CELL || _nv == SV_FACE))

3031/* begin storage definition section */
3032
3033/*
3034 * Parallel calls new_c() to build exterior cells before materials are
3035 * set. This eventually invokes the FLUID_THREAD_P macro which
3036 * breaks if the thread material is not set. A quick work-around
3037 * is to first check if the material is set. If not, return TRUE if
3038 * thread storage for the variable in question has already been
3039 * allocated.
3040 */
3041#if PARALLEL
3042# define FLUID_THREAD_OR_STORAGE_P(t,nv) ((NULLP(THREAD_MATERIAL(t))) ? (NNULLP(THREAD_STORAGE(t,nv))) : FLUID_THREAD_P(t))
3043# define SOLID_THREAD_OR_STORAGE_P(t,nv) ((NULLP(THREAD_MATERIAL(t))) ? (NNULLP(THREAD_STORAGE(t,nv))) : SOLID_THREAD_P(t))
3044# define FLUID_CELL_THREAD_OR_STORAGE_P(t,nv) (CELL_THREAD_P(t) && FLUID_THREAD_OR_STORAGE_P(t,nv))
3045# define SOLID_CELL_THREAD_OR_STORAGE_P(t,nv) (CELL_THREAD_P(t) && SOLID_THREAD_OR_STORAGE_P(t,nv))
3046#else
3047# define FLUID_THREAD_OR_STORAGE_P(t,nv) FLUID_THREAD_P(t)
3048# define FLUID_CELL_THREAD_OR_STORAGE_P(t,nv) FLUID_CELL_THREAD_P(t)
3049# define SOLID_CELL_THREAD_OR_STORAGE_P(t,nv) SOLID_CELL_THREAD_P(t)
3050#endif
3051
3052/* stringify the enumeration name
3053 sv: storage var enum
3054 pick: picking string
3055 name: display name
3056 dim: dimension enum for sizeof
3057 flag: allocation flags?
3058 init: initialization function pointer
3059 store:
3060 residual:
3061 eqn: associated equation?
3062 xfd: data id enum
3063 */
3064
3065#define SV(sv,pick,name,dim,flag,init,store,residual,eqn,xfd,xfr) \
3066{sv,#sv,pick,name,dim,flag,init,store,residual,eqn,xfd,xfr}
